---
import SidebarLayout from '../../../layouts/SidebarLayout.astro';
import "../../../styles/global.css";
---

<SidebarLayout app="c">
  <h1 class="text-xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-5 text-custom-accent text-center">
    Variables & Data Types in C
  </h1>

  <section class="mb-5 space-y-6 text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed text-custom-secondary">
    <p>
      Variables are used to store data in a program, and data types define the type of data that can be stored in variables.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mt-6 mb-3">Basic Data Types</h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="min-w-full border-collapse border border-custom text-sm sm:text-base">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-custom-secondary">
            <th class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2 text-custom-primary">Data Type</th>
            <th class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2 text-custom-primary">Size (bytes)</th>
            <th class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2 text-custom-primary">Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-custom-secondary">
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">int</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">4</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Stores integers</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">float</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">4</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Stores single-precision floating point numbers</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">double</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">8</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Stores double-precision floating point numbers</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">char</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">1</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Stores a single character</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mt-6 mb-3">Variable Declaration and Initialization</h2>

    <div class="bg-custom-secondary border border-custom rounded-lg p-3 sm:p-4 my-4">
      <pre class="text-xs sm:text-sm overflow-x-auto whitespace-pre-wrap"><code>{`#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    // Variable declaration
    int age;
    float salary;
    char grade;
    
    // Variable initialization
    age = 25;
    salary = 50000.50;
    grade = 'A';
    
    // Declaration and initialization in one line
    int score = 95;
    double percentage = 85.75;
    
    // Printing variables
    printf("Age: %d\\n", age);
    printf("Salary: %.2f\\n", salary);
    printf("Grade: %c\\n", grade);
    printf("Score: %d\\n", score);
    printf("Percentage: %.2f\\n", percentage);
    
    return 0;
}`}</code></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-custom-secondary border border-custom rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6 mt-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mb-3">Key Points</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 pl-4">
        <li>Variables must be declared before use</li>
        <li>C is case-sensitive (age and Age are different)</li>
        <li>Variable names can contain letters, digits, and underscores</li>
        <li>Variable names cannot start with a digit</li>
        <li>Use meaningful variable names for better code readability</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</SidebarLayout>